ESPN sports reporter Britt McHenry has been suspended for one week after video surfaced of her berating an employee at Advanced Towing in Arlington, Virginia . 
  The 28-year-old had her car towed from a Chinese restaurant and was filmed berating the woman for her looks and job . 
  She was warned she was being filmed but continued to insult the woman and her job . 
  ESPN said the incident occurred on April 6 . 
  McHenry was suspended from her job as a sideline reporter for ESPN in Washington D . 
 C . 
 